<item>
            <title>[SPR-2185] Null model assertion causes backwards compatibility issue</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2185</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Upgrading from 1.2.6 to 2.0 RC1 causes this to happen in some of my controllers:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Model object should not be null&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.springframework.util.Assert.notNull(Assert.java:113)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.springframework.ui.ModelMap.addObject(ModelMap.java:75)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.springframework.web.servlet.ModelAndView.addObject(ModelAndView.java:238)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s not really a big problem, but I thought you guys should be aware of it as it &lt;b&gt;does&lt;/b&gt; cause compatibility issues.  Out of curiosity, why can&apos;t we have a null model object?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
            <key id="14290">SPR-2185</key>
            <summary>Null model assertion causes backwards compatibility issue</summary>
